<a name=3D"lmm"></a>

<button class=3D"accordion">16. Effect Size for Linear Mixed Models (Cohen'=
s f=B2)</button>
<div class=3D"panel">	<br><br>
<p>Linear Mixed Models (LMMs) account for both fixed and random effects. Co=
hen's f=B2 can be computed from the model output to assess the effect size =
of fixed effects predictors. This implementation follows Gro=DF &amp; M=F6l=
ler (2025) and uses the variance-covariance matrix of the estimated fixed e=
ffects parameters. The effect size f=B2 is calculated as:</p>
<div align=3D"center">
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
	<msup><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msup>
	<mo>=3D</mo>
	<mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>&#957;</mi></mfrac>
	<msup>
		<mrow>
			<mo>(</mo>
			<msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub>
			<mover><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>^</mo></mover>
			<mo>)</mo>
		</mrow>
		<mi>T</mi>
	</msup>
	<msup>
		<mrow>
			<mo>(</mo>
			<msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub>
			<mover><mtext>Cov</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover>
			<mo>(</mo>
			<mover><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>^</mo></mover>
			<mo>)</mo>
			<msubsup><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn><mi>T</mi></msubsup>
			<mo>)</mo>
		</mrow>
		<mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow>
	</msup>
	<msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub>
	<mover><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>^</mo></mover>
</math>
</div>
<br>
<p>where &#957; =3D n - p are the degrees of freedom (n =3D sample size, p =
=3D number of fixed effects parameters).</p>

